{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 350°F.","Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Set scale to zero, then using a spoon, remove 5 oz of ground sugar (scale will show minus '- 5.0 oz') and reserve.","Add flour and salt and aerate <nobr>30 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla sugar (see Tip) into mixing bowl and without measuring cup whip <nobr>4 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>.","Again, without measuring cup whip <nobr>4-6 min\/120°F\/speed 3.5<\/nobr> slowly adding reserved ground sugar 1 tbsp at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid until soft peaks form.","Add beaten egg whites to reserved flour and gently fold in with spatula.","Transfer mixture into angel food cake pan and bake immediately for 35-40 minutes (350°F) until a skewer comes out clean and cracks appear dry. Invert pan and allow to cool completely (approx. 3 hours). Once cool unmold onto a platter and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 oz sugar","4 ½ oz cake flour","¼ tsp salt              (optional)","10 egg whites, (approx.14-15 oz), room temperature","1 ½ tsp cream of tartar","1 tsp vanilla sugar, homemade (see Tip)"]}],"id":"r105489","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-O8157XZ8uf8\/XZWrcJ3oPbI\/AAAAAAAAfnY\/Dc1DnYCMZdwhcWMj9nfiF5iwAyjmAuTnwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lco4zYsD3rd7cBDF.png","title":"Angel Food Cake","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"626 kJ \/ 150 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, non-stick angel food cake pan (9 in.-10 in.), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Cake texture is at its best when consumed within one day. To prevent from drying out, store in a container in the refrigerator. Angel Food Cake will keep for 4-5 days in the refrigerator or up to 1 month in the freezer.<br>If you don't have an angel food cake pan you can use a cake or tube pan and invert it over a bottle or a funnel to let angel food cake cool down.","Make your vanilla sugar before you start the recipe following the Vanilla Sugar recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","Angel Food Cake leftovers can be used for the cake base of trifle."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 10m","12 slices"]}